# World Happiness Report — Data Cleaning Pipeline

## Overview
A data cleaning pipeline built on the World Happiness Report dataset (2015–2019).
The goal is to produce a clean, analysis-ready dataset by handling missing values,
removing duplicates, standardising formatting, and flagging outliers.

## Dataset
Source: [Kaggle — World Happiness Report](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/unsdsn/world-happiness)  
Files: `2015.csv`, `2016.csv`, `2017.csv`, `2018.csv`, `2019.csv`

## What This Project Covers
- Auditing raw data (nulls, dtypes, duplicates, value counts)
- Handling missing values with appropriate imputation strategies
- Detecting and flagging outliers using IQR
- Standardising inconsistent string formatting
- Exporting a clean dataset and a summary of changes made

## How to Run
1. Clone the repo and navigate to this folder
2. Install dependencies: `pip install -r requirements.txt`
3. Run the script: `python main.py`

## Requirements
- Python 3.8+
- pandas
- numpy

